### dispatch() {#a15ee706711d88e4858baa2af17133ab6}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>virtual unsigned llvm::mca::LSUnitBase::dispatch (<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mca/instref">InstRef</a> &amp; IR)</>}>
Allocates LS resources for instruction IR.

This method assumes that a previous call to <code>isAvailable(IR)</code> succeeded with a <a href="#aaa2955db8dc3f1104bd78c37f6d883cd">LSUnitBase::Status</a> value of LSU&#95;AVAILABLE. Returns the GroupID associated with this instruction. That value will be used to set the LSUTokenID field in class <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mca/instruction">Instruction</a>.

### isAvailable() {#a4e3c49c1cddd6720166668d97871b923}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>virtual Status llvm::mca::LSUnitBase::isAvailable (<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mca/instref">InstRef</a> &amp; IR) const</>}>
This method checks the availability of the load/store buffers.

Returns LSU&#95;AVAILABLE if there are enough load/store queue entries to accomodate instruction IR. By default, LSU&#95;AVAILABLE is returned if IR is not a memory operation.

## Private Member Attributes

### LQSize {#ad6f39bba6f21ef12a19474bf3101fc97}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype="unsigned llvm::mca::LSUnitBase::LQSize">
Load queue size.

A value of zero for this field means that the load queue is unbounded. Processor models can declare the size of a load queue via tablegen (see the definition of tablegen class LoadQueue in llvm/Target/TargetSchedule.td).

### NoAlias {#af559128e984033174ea1daa584ffa476}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype="const bool llvm::mca::LSUnitBase::NoAlias">
True if loads don&#39;t alias with stores.

By default, the LS unit assumes that loads and stores don&#39;t alias with each other. If this field is set to false, then loads are always assumed to alias with stores.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/mca/include/llvm/mca/hardwareunits/lsunit-h/#l00053">53</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/mca/include/llvm/mca/hardwareunits/lsunit-h">LSUnit.h</a>.

Load queue size.

A value of zero for this field means that the store queue is unbounded. Processor models can declare the size of a store queue via tablegen (see the definition of tablegen class StoreQueue in llvm/Target/TargetSchedule.td).
